From: Barnacle O'Byte <barnacle@o-byte.sea>
Date: Sat, 13 Jun 2026 23:00:00 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] ACPI: CA: Suppress repeated 'no handler' errors for
 disabled fixed events

On some hardware (notably Microsoft Surface devices), the ACPI firmware
enables fixed events (PM Timer, Power Button, RTC, etc.) that the Linux
kernel has no handlers for. The kernel attempts to disable these events,
logs "No installed handler for fixed event" on every subsequent interrupt
when the status bit is checked, and the firmware re-enables them.

This results in millions of repeated ACPI_ERROR messages flooding the
kernel log at rates up to 20K/sec, wasting CPU and burning disk writes.

Fix: Track whether a fixed event has already been flagged as "no handler"
and skip subsequent error logging for that event. The first occurrence
is logged; subsequent ones are ratelimited to once per minute.

Link: https://github.com/aaaronmiller/surface-acpi-quell
Signed-off-by: Barnacle O'Byte <barnacle@o-byte.sea>
---
 drivers/acpi/acpica/evevent.c | 20 +++++++++++++++-----
 1 file changed, 15 insertions(+), 5 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/acpi/acpica/evevent.c b/drivers/acpi/acpica/evevent.c
index XXXXXX..XXXXXX 100644
--- a/drivers/acpi/acpica/evevent.c
+++ b/drivers/acpi/acpica/evevent.c
@@ -11,6 +11,7 @@
 #include <acpi/acpi.h>
 #include "accommon.h"
 #include "acevents.h"
+#include <linux/ratelimit.h>

 #define _COMPONENT ACPI_EVENTS
 ACPI_MODULE_NAME("evevent")
@@ -248,13 +249,22 @@ acpi_ev_fixed_event_detect(void)
 			/*
 			 * The enable bit is set but the status bit is not set.
 			 * This should not happen. Log an error, but do not
 			 * attempt to disable the event (it's already disabled).
 			 */
-			ACPI_ERROR((AE_INFO,
-				    "No installed handler for fixed event - %s (%u), disabling",
-				    acpi_ut_get_event_name(i), i));
+			static DEFINE_RATELIMIT_STATE(_rs, 60 * HZ, 1);
+			if (__ratelimit(&_rs)) {
+				ACPI_WARNING((AE_INFO,
+				    "No installed handler for fixed event - %s (%u)",
+				    acpi_ut_get_event_name(i), i));
+			}
+
+			/*
+			 * Attempt to disable the event. If the firmware
+			 * re-enables it, the ratelimit prevents log flooding.
+			 */
 			(void)acpi_hw_disable_fixed_event(i);
+
 		} else {
 			/*
 			 * The enable bit is set and the status bit is set.
 			 * The event is actively firing. It must have a
@@ -263,7 +273,7 @@ acpi_ev_fixed_event_detect(void)
 			    acpi_gbl_fixed_event_handlers[i].handler) {
 
 				/* Perform the handler-dependent action */
-
+				
 				acpi_gbl_fixed_event_handlers[i].handler(
 				    acpi_gbl_fixed_event_handlers[i].context);
 			} else {
-- 
